					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Oh this could explain things. I don't think they made PAL or NTSC TVs anymore, they just make them worldwide universal (or does they ?). My TV let me chose between 4 audio decoding systems : SC1 (which works for the PAL (S)NES), SC2, SC3 and F. No idea what this means, but neither of those works. I can get some audio trough the noise in FF3, and ONLY in FF3 (which is really weird), with SC1. F also kills the video which is weird.
<br />
<br />And I can confirm switches are identical in NTSC and PAL countries. The only difference is the mechanics of the connectors. I don't know if it recognize a signal producted by the console, but I doubt. The switch is optional for the NTSC console - the image works fine without it (but sound doesn't work no matter what). For the PAL console, the image is noisy without the switch (which is werid).
<br />
<br />Also all my problems does not depends on the power supply - I tried an alternate 8.5V DC supply and it is the same as when using the 9V AC supply.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
